Date: 4 Jun 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: WHO SARS website/ Beijing SARS website [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/sars/chinatable2003_06_4.pdf>
<http://www.beijing.gov.cn/english/englishsars/beijingen/detail.asp?ResourceID=63257>

[The Beijing Government SARS website link is changed daily, but the
WHO website maintains each daily report in archives. - Mod.MPP]
[As of 4 Jun 2003 there are a cumulative total of 5329 probable
cases of SARS with 334 deaths reported in mainland China. In the
past 24 hours there have been no reports of new probable cases or of
any deaths due to SARS. There are an additional 908 suspected cases
pending (down from 982 on 1 Jun 2003, 965 on 2 Jun 2003, and 929 on 3
Jun 2003, representing net exclusions of reported suspected cases).
There were reports of 4 suspected cases, with 2 from Beijing and 1
each from Guangdong and Sichuan. - Mod.MPP]
At the moment, 1321 patients are receiving treatment in hospitals.
According to WHO statistical criteria, as of 10 am, 4 Jun 2003, SARS
exists in 12 provinces. The following provinces did not report new
probable cases in the past 15 or more days: Tianjin, Jilin,
Guangdong, Guangxi. Hubei, Shanghai, and Sichuan have not reported
new probable cases in the past 10 or more days. Shanxi and Inner
Mongolia have not reported new probable cases in the past 9 days.
Hebei has not reported new probable cases in the past 6 days.
Overall, 25 suspect cases were excluded from Beijing (8), Guangdong
(4), Hebei (1), Inner Mongolia (7), Shanxi (3), Liaoning (1), Fujian
(1)
As of 10 AM, 4 Jun 2003, there were 908 total cumulative suspect
cases in China Mainland.
In the 20-day period from 10 AM 16 May 2003 to 10 AM 4 Jun 2003, a
total of 268 new probable cases were reported. 63 of these cases were
reported directly as new clinically confirmed (probable) cases
[Beijing (44), Hebei (6), Shanxi (4), Guangdong (4), Tianjin (2),
Jilin (1), Guangxi (2), Inner Mongolia (0), Liaoning (0), Sichuan
(0), Shanghai (0), and Hubei (0) ]. 205 of these were first reported
as suspect cases and then reclassified as probable cases [Beijing
(146) , Hebei (27), Shanxi (8), Tianjin (2), Jilin (2), Inner
Mongolia (11), Liaoning (4), Sichuan (3), Shanghai (1), and Hubei (1)]
Total numbers include the subtotals of the following 14 provinces/
autonomous regions/ municipalities that are not shown: Heilongjiang,
Xinjiang, Gansu, Jiangsu, Anhui, Shaanxi, Zhejiang, Henan, Chongqing,
Jiangxi, Ningxia, Shandong, Fujian, Hunan. For the provinces not
shown, the number of discharged cases reported in this 24-hour period
is 3; 1 previously reported suspect case was excluded in the 24-hour
period. The cumulative number of probable cases is 75; the cumulative
number of suspect cases is 15; the cumulative number of discharged
cases is 62; the cumulative number of deaths is 4.
Today China Mainland reported no new probable cases, 116 discharges,
and zero deaths. The 116 discharges were from Beijijng (74), Hebei
(10), Tianjin (11), Shanxi (6), Inner Mongolia (9), Jiangsu (2),
Guangdong (2), Jilin (1), Gansu (1).
In the 24-hour period, there were a total of 4 new suspect cases
reported from 3 provinces: Beijing (2), Guangdong (1), and Sichuan
(1).
Case reports were received from 31 provinces/autonomous regions/municipalities.
