Source: News brief [edited]
[A] Germany from yahoo news Germany, submitted by Gerhard Mosbach
<info@meil.de> <http://de.news.yahoo.com/030604/3/3h5xg.html> [trans.
by Mod.MPP]
A 60-year-old male engineer returning from Taiwan was admitted to a
hospital in Hamburg with a suspicion of SARS. As a result, 50
contacts were placed in quarantine. This was announced by the Robert
Koch Institute on 4 Jun 2003. This is the 11th case of SARS reported
in Germany.
--
