<promed@promedmail.org>
[As of 4 Jun 2003 there have been a cumulative total of 8402 probable
cases of SARS with 772 deaths reported from 29 countries. In the
past 24 hours there have been 10 new probable cases reported, with
Canada reporting 5 new cases, Taiwan 2 new cases, and 1 each from
Hong Kong, Germany, and the United States. No deaths were reported
in the preceding 24 hours. There were no new probable cases reported
from China in the past 24 hours.
The newswires had rumors suggesting there may be some imported cases
associated with travel to Canada, but these are just speculations and
have not been confirmed. As of 1 PM 4 Jun 2003, 3 new probable and 3
new suspected cases have been reported in Canada; the most recent
date of onset of probable cases in Canada was 31 May 2003; and of
suspected cases, 28 May 2003 (unchanged from yesterday's report). -
Mod.MPP]
